## What It Does

**Clinical Doppelgänger** is a SMART on FHIR clinical decision support application that answers one question:

> **"Among patients who were clinically similar to this patient at a comparable stage, what happened to them — and why?"**

Instead of producing a single risk score, the app surfaces **historical patient trajectories** from a cohort, ranked by statistical similarity to the current patient. Each match shows:

- How similar they were (cosine similarity %)
- What happened (improved / hospitalized / deteriorated)
- When it happened (Kaplan-Meier time-to-event)
- Why they were matched (explainability panel)
- What turned their trajectory (key clinical event)

This is **case-based reasoning**, not prediction. The distinction is intentional and clinically safer.

---

## Live Demo

Open `index.html` directly in a browser → **auto-falls back to demo mode** with 3 synthetic patients and a 5-patient comparison cohort. No server required.

To connect to a real FHIR sandbox:

```
1. Host files on GitHub Pages (or any static server)
2. Go to: https://launch.smarthealthit.org
3. App Launch URL:   https://your-username.github.io/your-repo/launch.html
4. FHIR Version:     R4
5. Launch type:      Provider EHR Launch
6. Click Launch → select a patient
```

