## How to Run

### Option A — Instant demo (no setup)
```bash
# Just open the file
open index.html
# or use VS Code Live Server (recommended for FHIR flow)
```

### Option B — GitHub Pages + SMART sandbox
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Clinical Doppelganger v3"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USER/YOUR_REPO.git
git push -u origin main
# Enable Pages in: Settings → Pages → Branch: main → Save
```
Then register at [launch.smarthealthit.org](https://launch.smarthealthit.org) using your `launch.html` URL.

### Option C — Local FHIR server
Edit `launch.html` and set `clientId` to match your registered app credentials.

