## UI Tabs & Components

| Tab | Key Components | Data Source |
|---|---|---|
| **Overview** | Clinical fingerprint cards, PSM report, cohort stats with 95% CI, stacked outcome bar, adjusted outcome comparison, similarity bar chart | `buildVector`, `computePSM`, `bootstrapCI`, `buildAdjusted` |
| **Survival** | Kaplan-Meier 3-curve chart, Markov transition table | `buildKMCurve`, `buildMarkov` |
| **Analytics** | Trajectory cluster cards, patient vs cohort radar chart | `buildClusters`, cohort average vectors |
| **Matches** | Filterable ranked doppelgänger cards, expandable timeline, match-reason explainability, turning-point annotation | `cosine`, `DEMO_COHORT` |

---

## Academic Framing

### One-sentence description
> **"A trajectory-aware, propensity-score-matched cohort retrieval system for clinical decision support using SMART on FHIR."**

### Statistical pipeline summary
```
Raw FHIR data
    ↓  buildVector()
11-dimensional feature vector
    ↓  cosine()
Similarity-ranked cohort (top-K)
    ↓  computePSM()
Propensity-balanced cohort (SMD < 0.1)
    ↓  bootstrapCI()
95% confidence intervals on outcomes
    ↓  buildKMCurve()
Kaplan-Meier time-to-event curves
    ↓  buildMarkov()
State transition probabilities
    ↓  buildClusters()
Trajectory phenotype subtypes
```

### Why this is NOT a prediction model

The app intentionally avoids framing results as predictions for three reasons:

1. **Observational data** from FHIR cannot establish causality
2. **Small cohort** (sandbox: ~100 patients) is underpowered for individual prediction
3. **Clinical safety** — presenting a probability (e.g., "72% chance of hospitalization") invites over-reliance; presenting trajectories invites clinical reasoning

Instead, the app says: *"Among similar patients, outcomes varied. Here is the distribution."*

---

## Limitations & Future Work

| Limitation | Mitigation / Future Direction |
|---|---|
| Small demo cohort (n=5) | Replace with FHIR Bulk Data API (`$export`) for population-level cohort |
| Simulated PSM coefficients | Fit logistic model on real EHR data using `sklearn` backend |
| No missing data handling | Add imputation for missing HbA1c / BP values |
| Single time-point snapshot | Incorporate longitudinal FHIR observations for temporal fingerprinting |
| No survival censoring | Add right-censoring indicator to KM estimator |
| K-means cluster count fixed at 3 | Add elbow method / silhouette score to determine optimal K |
| Cosine similarity only | Implement Mahalanobis distance (accounts for feature covariance) |
| Client-side only | Add Node.js backend for richer statistical computation |

